In the year, etc. In presence of me notary public and witness-es underwritten personally appeared a venerable and worthy man Master John Colquhoun provost of Bothanis und dean of the christianity of Peblis at the instance and request of an honest man John Hay brother germanos Thomas Hay of Smeithfeild, and went personally to the perpetual preeeptory of the hospital of Str. Leonard founded for ever at the burgh of Perdis, having and holding in his hands a certain gift of the said perpetual prceeptory by our sovereign lady the Queen under her privy seal, and there the said John delivered the said gift to th'e said master John and humbly re- quested him sorthwith to put the said letter of gift to due execution, which letter of gift the said master John received with due reverence, and delivered tho same to me, notary public subscribing to be read published and explained in the common tonguc.
